Interface IuResource<T>

public interface IuResource<T> extends Supplier<T>
Facade interface for a resource declared by a component.

    • factory

      Supplier<?> factory()
      Gets the factory to be used for creating new instances.

      By default, returns a Supplier that:

      • Returns IuType.autoboxDefault() if the resource type is an immutable single-value
      • Invokes IuExecutable.exec(Object...) on an an internally managed implementation class or InvocationHandler suitable for representing the resource
      Returns:
      factory that supplies new instance of the resource, or an InvocationHandler for backing a Proxy.

    • factory

      void factory(Supplier<?> factory)
      Provides a factory to use for creating new instances of the resource.

      The factory may return:

      • A direct instance of the resource class.
      • A instance of a class that implements the resource interface
      • An InvocationHandler to back a Proxy for the resource interface

      To selective override default behavior, call factory() first to get a reference to the default factory.

      Parameters:
      factory - resource implementation factory.

    • get

      T get()
      Gets the resource value.

      Provides a new or immutable instance when shared() returns false; may provide the same instance on subsequent calls when shared() returns true.

      Specified by:
      get in interface Supplier<T>
